cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of detecting and mapping solar photovoltaic arrays in aerial imagery using a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of aerial imagery and robotics for energy resource assessment could also place it in cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques to estimate the surface area of PV arrays, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
